contentrichtext.text: '''Northwest Hancock''' is an [[unorganized territory]] (township) in [[Hancock County, Maine|Hancock County]], [[Maine]], [[United States]]. The population was 4 at the [[2000 United States Census|2000 census]]. The territory is designated as Township 32 Middle Division. ==Geography== According to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the unorganized territory has a total area of 41.4 square miles (107.3 km²), 41.3 square miles (107.1 km²) of it is land and 0.1 square miles (0.2 km²) of it is water (0.22%). ==Demographics== As of the [[census]]{{GR|2}} of 2000.there were 4 people, 2 households, and 1 family residing in the unorganized territory. The [[population density]] was 0.1 people per square mile (0.0/km²). There were 20 housing units at an average density of 0.5/sq mi (0.2/km²). The racial makeup of the unorganized territory was 100.00% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]]. There were 2 households out of which 1 was a [[Marriage|married couple]] living together, and 1 was a non-family. No households were made up of individuals and none had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2 and the average family size was 2. All of the inhabitants were 45 to 64 years old. The median age was 50 years. For every 100 females there were 100 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over there were 100 males. ==References== <references /> {{Hancock County, Maine}} {{coord|44|56|11|N|68|25|57|W|display=title}} [[Category:Unorganized territories in Maine]] [[Category:Populated places in Hancock County, Maine]]
